<div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">
</div>
<table align="center" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" class="tr-caption-container" style="margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; text-align: center;"><tbody>
<tr><td style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/-9PvPAhGroVg/U7GxMYjLK9I/AAAAAAAAALQ/x2Ppy418Yc4/s1600/final.png" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;"><img border="0" src="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/-9PvPAhGroVg/U7GxMYjLK9I/AAAAAAAAALQ/x2Ppy418Yc4/s1600/final.png" height="480" width="640" /></a></td></tr>
<tr><td class="tr-caption" style="text-align: center;">Using a Sublime Text Build System to execute a script via SQL*Plus</td></tr>
</tbody></table>
<br />
<a href="http://www.sublimetext.com/">Sublime Text</a> supports the creation of build systems which, as per the <a href="http://sublimetext.info/docs/en/reference/build_systems.html">Unofficial Documentation</a>, allows to "run external programs to process your project’s files and print captured output to the output panel". Furthermore, the captured output can be parsed to capture error information and "When error information is captured, you can navigate to error instances in your project’s files with F4 and Shift+F4. If available, the captured error message will be displayed in the status bar."<br />
<br />
As I usually code stored procedures on a text editor and load them to the database via SQL*Plus, this could save me a step and even allow to easily navigate to reported error locations, if any.<br />
<br />
To create a New build system we proceed to do the following steps.<br />
<br />
Go to the Tools Menu, select the Build System submenu and then the New Build System… option. This will create a untitled file with the .sublime-build extension and the following content:<br />
<div style="font-family: Calibri; font-size: 11.0pt; margin: 0in;">
<br /></div>
<div style="margin: 0in;">
<pre class="textmate-source"><span class="source source_json"><span class="meta meta_structure meta_structure_dictionary meta_structure_dictionary_json"><span class="punctuation punctuation_definition punctuation_definition_dictionary punctuation_definition_dictionary_begin punctuation_definition_dictionary_begin_json">{</span>
  <span class="string string_quoted string_quoted_double string_quoted_double_json"><span class="punctuation punctuation_definition punctuation_definition_string punctuation_definition_string_begin punctuation_definition_string_begin_json">"</span>cmd<span class="punctuation punctuation_definition punctuation_definition_string punctuation_definition_string_end punctuation_definition_string_end_json">"</span></span><span class="meta meta_structure meta_structure_dictionary meta_structure_dictionary_value meta_structure_dictionary_value_json"><span class="punctuation punctuation_separator punctuation_separator_dictionary punctuation_separator_dictionary_key-value punctuation_separator_dictionary_key-value_json">:</span> <span class="meta meta_structure meta_structure_array meta_structure_array_json"><span class="punctuation punctuation_definition punctuation_definition_array punctuation_definition_array_begin punctuation_definition_array_begin_json">[</span><span class="string string_quoted string_quoted_double string_quoted_double_json"><span class="punctuation punctuation_definition punctuation_definition_string punctuation_definition_string_begin punctuation_definition_string_begin_json">"</span>make<span class="punctuation punctuation_definition punctuation_definition_string punctuation_definition_string_end punctuation_definition_string_end_json">"</span></span><span class="punctuation punctuation_definition punctuation_definition_array punctuation_definition_array_end punctuation_definition_array_end_json">]</span></span>
</span><span class="punctuation punctuation_definition punctuation_definition_dictionary punctuation_definition_dictionary_end punctuation_definition_dictionary_end_json">}</span></span></span></pre>
</div>
<br />
<!--StartFragment-->



<!--EndFragment--><br />
<div style="font-family: Calibri; font-size: 11.0pt; margin: 0in;">
</div>
Replace with the following to call sqlplus from the command line:<br />
