</div>
<div style="font-family: Calibri; font-size: 11.0pt; margin: 0in;">
<span style="font-size: 11pt;"><br /></span></div>
<div style="font-size: 11.0pt; margin: 0in;">
</div>
Edit the connection information ("scott/tiger@xe") on line 2 to match with the one corresponding to the database this is to be used for.  Lines 3 and 4 are to be used for capturing error information.<br />
<br />
Now, save the file (CTRL+S) and a dialog will appear to specify a name. The appropriate location will be already selected (e.g. %APPDATA%/Roaming/Sublime Text 2/Packages/User if on Windows). Change the untitled name with a meaningful one that relates with the database this is to be used for.<br />
<div style="font-family: Calibri; font-size: 11.0pt; margin: 0in;">
<br /></div>
<table align="center" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" class="tr-caption-container" style="margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; text-align: center;"><tbody>
<tr><td style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/--S0FzPzPzt8/U7GxvMutAbI/AAAAAAAAALY/7x8-2LH8wJI/s1600/file_name.png" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;"><img border="0" src="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/--S0FzPzPzt8/U7GxvMutAbI/AAAAAAAAALY/7x8-2LH8wJI/s1600/file_name.png" height="66" width="320" /></a></td></tr>
<tr><td class="tr-caption" style="text-align: center;">Specify the Build System file name, which will be used also when displaying on the Menu</td></tr>
</tbody></table>
<div style="font-family: Calibri; font-size: 11.0pt; margin: 0in;">
<br /></div>
<div style="font-family: Calibri; font-size: 11.0pt; margin: 0in;">
<!--StartFragment-->



<!--EndFragment--></div>
Once the file is saved it will appear on the Build System Menu, after the default ones.<br />
<div style="font-family: Calibri; font-size: 11.0pt; margin: 0in;">
<br /></div>
<table align="center" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" class="tr-caption-container" style="margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; text-align: center;"><tbody>
<tr><td style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/-nlrtquKRxmA/U7Gx8wRarTI/AAAAAAAAALg/5qn9ZHDUfNs/s1600/bild_system_menu.png" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;"><img border="0" src="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/-nlrtquKRxmA/U7Gx8wRarTI/AAAAAAAAALg/5qn9ZHDUfNs/s1600/bild_system_menu.png" height="230" width="320" /></a></td></tr>
<tr><td class="tr-caption" style="text-align: center;">Build System menu, listing custom ones on the bottom</td></tr>
</tbody></table>
<div style="font-family: Calibri; font-size: 11.0pt; margin: 0in;">
Now, when you are ready to compile a source file to the database, select the appropriate Build System (a checkmark will appear next to it) and it will remain the selected until a different one is chosen.</div>
<div style="font-family: Calibri; font-size: 11.0pt; margin: 0in;">
<br /></div>
<div style="font-family: Calibri; font-size: 11.0pt; margin: 0in;">
<!--StartFragment-->



<!--EndFragment--></div>
<table align="center" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" class="tr-caption-container" style="margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; text-align: center;"><tbody>
<tr><td style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/-tTmitaNiZLA/U7GyLjsobNI/AAAAAAAAALo/2gkO_pXPPSg/s1600/build_system_select.png" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;"><img border="0" src="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/-tTmitaNiZLA/U7GyLjsobNI/AAAAAAAAALo/2gkO_pXPPSg/s1600/build_system_select.png" /></a></td></tr>
<tr><td class="tr-caption" style="text-align: center;">Checkmark denotes which Build System is selected</td></tr>
</tbody></table>
To test the build system, I created a file with the following content which has a syntax error to test the error capture feature:<br />
