<div>
As it can be seen, compilation errors are found, but not displayed. We would usually use the show errors command, but it sometimes is not reliable and can also fail to show information when creating objects under an schema different to the one we are connecting with. The alternative is to query the dba_errors table (or user_errors if not having access to it). The script now becomes the following:</div>
<div>
<div>
<br /></div>
</div>
<div>
<pre class="textmate-source"><span class="source source_oracle"><span class="comment comment_line comment_line_double-dash">-- Execution related substitution variables</span>
