<br />
The screen capture below shows that the error message is displayed on the status bar and the corresponding line (16) is highlighted on the source file. As the column is also captured, the cursor will be also positioned on it.<br />
<br />
The only caveat, if you haven't noticed, is the use of an offset to properly identify the line number for the error within the script. As Oracle reports the line number of the actual source (starting at wherever the CREATE statement is located), we need to account for as many lines as we have on the script before it. Line 6 (define b_off = 13) is used to store the offset value which is 13 in this example as the create or replace package line is located on row 14.<br />
